ðŸ”¹ Abstraction â€“ Interview Answer

Abstraction is an OOPS concept that shows only essential information to the user and hides the internal implementation details.
It focuses on what an object does rather than how it does it.

ðŸ”¹ Real-Life Example

A car is a simple example of abstraction.
The driver uses pedals and steering without knowing how the engine works internally.

ðŸ”¹ How Abstraction Is Achieved in Java

In Java, abstraction is achieved using abstract classes and interfaces.

ðŸ”¹ Why Abstraction Is Important

Abstraction reduces complexity, improves security, and makes code easier to maintain.

ðŸ”¹ One-Line Closing

Abstraction hides complexity and exposes only what is necessary.

ðŸ”¥ Ultra-Short Revision (30 seconds)

